Kohinoor Inventory Management System

Functional & Non-Functional Requirements

Introduction
This document presents the functional and non-functional requirements of the Kohinoor Inventory Management System, a Flutter-based mobile application using Firebase backend for managing inventory of blades, machines, and spare parts.
Functional Requirements

FR01: The system shall allow users to log in using registered credentials.
FR02: The system shall allow authorized users to log out securely.
FR03: The system shall allow adding new inventory items.
FR04: The system shall allow updating inventory items.
FR05: The system shall allow deleting inventory items.
FR06: The system shall display inventory list.
FR07: The system shall support item search.
FR08: The system shall track item quantities.
FR09: The system shall update stock in real-time.
FR10: The system shall categorize inventory.
FR11: The system shall show item details.
FR12: The system shall store data in Firebase.
FR13: The system shall sync data across devices.
FR14: The system shall restrict access to owners.
FR15: The system shall show low-stock alerts.
FR16: The system shall provide dashboard statistics.
FR17: The system shall log inventory changes.
FR18: The system shall refresh data manually.
FR19: The system shall validate user input.
FR20: The system shall support future feature expansion.

Non-Functional Requirements
Performance: Fast response and real-time updates.
Security: Firebase authentication and access control.
Usability: Simple and intuitive UI.
Reliability: High availability and data recovery.
Scalability: Supports growth in users and data.
Maintainability: Modular and clean codebase.
Compatibility: Works on Android devices.
